Use `ConfigureLifecycleEvents` in `MauiProgram.cs`:

```csharp
builder.ConfigureLifecycleEvents(events =>
{
#if ANDROID
    events.AddAndroid(android => android
        .OnPause(activity =>
        {
            // App losing focus (partially backgrounded)
        })
        .OnStop(activity =>
        {
            // App fully backgrounded
        }));
#elif IOS || MACCATALYST
    events.AddiOS(ios => ios
        .DidEnterBackground(app =>
        {
            // App entered background
        }));
#endif
});
```

**Key points:**

- `OnPause` (Android) maps to the cross-platform `Deactivated` event (app loses focus but may still be visible).
- `OnStop` (Android) and `DidEnterBackground` (iOS) both map to the cross-platform `Stopped` event (fully backgrounded).
- If you don't need platform-specific APIs, you can use the simpler cross-platform `Window.Stopped` event instead — it fires on both platforms when the app backgrounds.
- Keep handlers fast (<2s) to avoid ANR on Android or watchdog kills on iOS.
